    "These embeddings are iteratively updated and at each iteration (layer), a new embedding is calculated for each node.",
    "In most cases, an activation function is also employed to induce nonlinearity (Chehreghani 2022).",
    "This process can be described as a message-passing mechanism (Gilmer et al. 2017).",
    "Each node follows three steps: 1) it gathers the embedding vectors of all its neighbors (message passing), 2) it applies an aggregation function to the gathered messages, and 3) it updates its own embedding vector, accordingly.",
